hands_on_practices.problem:
Let $G$ be a finite group with an order of 72. Suppose there exists a non-identity element $g \in G$ such that its order, denoted as $\text{ord}(g)$, is a prime number. Which of the following options represents the complete set of all possible values for $\text{ord}(g)$?

A. {2, 3}

B. {1, 2, 3}

C. {2}

D. {3}

E. {2, 3, 7}
